rent, at moderate\nvalues of $l_\\mathrm{Hall}/a$, stimulates the emerging of KHI of the kink ($m =\n1)$ and high-mode ($m \\geqslant 2$) MHD waves, while for the sausage wave ($m =\n0$) the trend is just the opposite---the KHI is suppressed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 2 Feb 2020 12:29:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-11"}
